TITLE: 2024 Watch: DeSantis tops Trump by double digits in second straight GOP presidential primary poll
SUMMARY: A new poll of Republican primary voters suggests Forida Gov. Ron DeSantis topping former President Donald Trump by 14 points in a hypothetical 2024 GOP presidential nomination showdown

TITLE: Newsom says California about to 'break' amid flood of illegal migrants when Title 42 expires
SUMMARY: Gov. Gavin Newsom of California warned that the Biden administration's plans to repeal Trump-era Title 42 immigration policies could "break" his state.

TITLE: Left wing group releases 'Don't Run, Joe' ad opposing Biden reelection bid
SUMMARY: A new ad from a progressive group depicts New Hampshire voters calling on President Biden to step aside and not run for reelection in the 2024 presidential election.

TITLE: DOJ official says Dobbs decision ramps up 'urgency' to enforce FACE Act, protect reproductive services
SUMMARY: A Justice Department official said the Supreme Court overturning Roe v. Wade has increased the Civil Rights Division's "urgency" to protect reproductive services.

TITLE: Congress achieves 'framework' for omnibus spending bill to avert government shutdown
SUMMARY: House and Senate negotiators said late Tuesday they reached a deal on a framework for a spending bill that will keep the government open through fiscal year 2023.

TITLE: House Republicans demand testimony from Biden officials, experts on COVID-19 origins, virus research in Wuhan
SUMMARY: House Republicans will call 40 officials to testify regarding the origins of COVID-19 as well as U.S. funding for virus research in Wuhan, leadership announced Wednesday.

TITLE: GOP gov eyes White House bid, calls Trump nomination 'worst scenario' for party
SUMMARY: Republican Arkansas Gov. Asa Hutchinson said he is looking into possibly running for president in 2024, and warned against his party nominating former President Donald Trump.

TITLE: White House glows rainbow colors after Biden signs Respect For Marriage Act
SUMMARY: The White House was glowing with rainbow colors after the Respect for Marriage Act was signed into law Tuesday afternoon. President Biden hosted a signing ceremony earlier in the day.

TITLE: FBI may have violated First Amendment with Twitter moderation requests, experts warn
SUMMARY: Constitutional experts tell Fox News Digital the FBI may have violated the First Amendment by asking Twitter to moderate tweets, as revealed in the new "Twitter Files."

TITLE: Top Republican calls for probe into Biden admin's vetting of non-binary official facing prison time
SUMMARY: Sen. John Barrasso, the top GOP member of the Senate Energy Committee, is calling on the Department of Energy to answer questions about its vetting and security clearance process.

TITLE: DHS Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas travels to southern border as Republicans call for his impeachment
SUMMARY: Alejandro Mayorkas, the secretary of homeland security, went to Texas to speak with U.S. Customs and Border Protection about the crisis at the border.

TITLE: Biden admin seeks $4 billion in additional border funding, predicts post-Title 42 border surge
SUMMARY: The Biden administration is requesting $4 billion in DHS funding as it faces a potential surge in migrant encounters at the southern border once Title 42 ends next week.

TITLE: Veterans Affairs sued over new abortion rule after Roe rollback that allegedly violates religious liberty
SUMMARY: A lawsuit against the Department of Veterans Affairs alleges the agency is violating the First Amendment with a new rule allowing abortions to be provided by the department.

TITLE: Biden denounces GOP states that limit child gender surgeries during same-sex marriage bill-signing ceremony
SUMMARY: The president signed the Respect for Marriage Act into law Tuesday with numerous guests ranging from cabinet members, lawmakers and non-binary drag queens at the White House.

TITLE: 20 House Republicans push Congress to impeach DHS chief Alejandro Mayorkas
SUMMARY: Twenty Republicans demanded on Tuesday that the U.S. House of Representatives impeach Department of Homeland Security Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas next Congress.

TITLE: Poll shows Biden's low level of support in 2024 among Democratic primary voters
SUMMARY: A new Five Thirty Eight/Ipsos poll revealed that President Joe Biden and Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis are the two frontrunners

TITLE: Teen charged in shooting outside Rep. Lee Zeldin's home indicted in New York gang takedown
SUMMARY: The accused gunman in a shooting outside Rep. Lee Zeldin's home, 18-year-old Noah Green, is among alleged gang members charged in a new 148-count indictment in Suffolk County, New York.

TITLE: GOP bill would protect parents who refuse to transition their child's gender
SUMMARY: A bill introduced Tuesday by Rep. Virginia Foxx, R-N.C., seeks to protect parents who refuse to transition their child's gender, either socially or medically.

SUMMARY: Get the latest updates from the 2024 campaign trail, exclusive interviews and more Fox News politics content

TITLE: LGBTQ activist exposed by Rep. Nancy Mace: ‘Do you believe your rhetoric is a threat to democracy?’
SUMMARY: Rep. Nancy Mace on Tuesday exposed a transgender activist for saying violent rhetoric is dangerous, even though she has called for violence against the Supreme Court.
